## Relay-P11 Agent Response Speed Optimization
**Status:** in_progress
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** Relay-P1, Relay-P2, Runtime-G2

Systematic optimization of Relay Pipeline latency. Phase 1 and 2 completed; Phase 3 partially completed.

### Root Cause Analysis

| Priority | Issue | Location | Estimated Impact |
|----------|-------|----------|-----------------|
| P0 | Agent recreated per step (ephemeral design) | `drive_run` → `build_agent()` | 50–500ms handoff overhead |
| P0 | `std::sync::Mutex` blocks tokio worker threads | `RunStore` definition | Thread starvation under concurrency |
| P1 | Synchronous I/O in async runtime | `shell`, `search`, `list_symbols` tools | 10s+ stalls (`cargo test`) |
| P2 | No connection warm-up | `ClaudeProvider::new()` | 50–300ms TLS handshake per first request |
| P2 | Deep clone of messages/tools per ReAct turn | `ToolChatRequest` construction | Grows with conversation length |
| P3 | Gate polling busy-wait | `tokio::time::sleep(2s)` | Minor, tolerable |

### Phase 1 — Agent Lifecycle Optimization (Completed)

| Task | Owner | Duration | Status |
|------|-------|----------|--------|
| Relay-P11.1 | Profile handoff overhead: `build_agent`, `RelayRegistry::new`, `ToolRegistry::new` | Core | 1 day | Done |
| Relay-P11.2 | Memoize `RelayRegistry` — cache parsed configs across steps | Core | 2 days | Done |
| Relay-P11.3 | Memoize `ToolRegistry` — build once per profession, reuse | Core | 1 day | Done |
| Relay-P11.4 | Pre-render system prompts — cache soul + spec context | Core | 1 day | Done |

### Phase 2 — Concurrency & I/O Optimization (Completed)

| Task | Owner | Duration | Status |
|------|-------|----------|--------|
| Relay-P11.5 | Replace `std::sync::Mutex` with `tokio::sync::RwLock` in `RunStore` | Core | 2 days | Done |
| Relay-P11.6 | Move `save_run` disk I/O out of lock — use background task | Core | 1 day | Done |
| Relay-P11.7 | Make `shell` tool async (`tokio::process::Command`) | Core | 1 day | Done |
| Relay-P11.8 | Make `search` tool async (streaming walk + yield) | Core | 2 days | Done |

### Phase 3 — Connection & Memory Optimization (In Progress)

| Task | Owner | Duration | Status |
|------|-------|----------|--------|
| Relay-P11.9 | Add connection warm-up request in `ClaudeProvider::new()` | Core | 1 day | In Progress |
| Relay-P11.10 | Tune `reqwest::Client` connection pool for high concurrency | Core | 0.5 day | Pending |
| Relay-P11.11 | Replace deep clone with `Arc<Messages>` + cow pattern | Core | 2 days | Pending |
| Relay-P11.12 | Gate notification via `tokio::sync::Notify` instead of polling | Core | 1 day | Pending |

### References

- ClaudeCode Bootstrap design: Fast-path dispatch, module-level parallel I/O, promise parallelism, memoized init
- Key insight: ClaudeCode's Agent is long-lived (one query loop); AutoForge's Agent is per-step. Move toward "warm-up and reuse" model.

